{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a31c95ad-3221-4ab5-84d1-7f789c1c6783","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped VSTest support by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk **3.8**, the default test runner switched to **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new `--` runner). In **4.x**, the VSTest compatibility layer was **removed entirely**, so `vstest.console` can no longer discover or run tests from these projects.\n\n### How to fix\n\n**Option A — Switch your CI to the new runner** (recommended):\n\n```bash\n# Replace vstest.console with direct execution:\ndotnet test TestProject.csproj\n# or run the built executable directly:\n./TestProject --list-tests\n./TestProject\n```\n\n**Option B — Re-enable VSTest compatibility** by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nOr if you truly need `vstest.console`, pin back to the older SDK or set `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` (if still supported in your version).\n\n**Option A** is the recommended long-term path since Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the future of .NET testing.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d08d4a53-6dfc-4891-bd7d-ebfe838538a3","outputTokens":308,"requestId":"3406:2C2C7B:FCDE6D:1293A71:69F41635"},"id":"692424fd-26e6-4ecb-86b6-d7673c2c67e4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:55:58.965Z","parentId":"c5240479-c93f-484a-ba5a-b7c042f320c3"}
